nodes.bodyText:
I figured we should have an explicit discussion about that even though we chatted briefly several months ago. catbird-util is the only dependency of finch-core that also requires finagle-http, which means we usually have to publish it first (well, Travis has to). Shame on me, I completely forgot about that last time I did a release so we did it later (see #788).
I think having Rerunnable defined under io.finch.internal would go a long way in simplifying our release process and the dependency graph. So I'm voting for forking it in 0.16 and dropping the catbird-util dependency.
@travisbrown, @rpless what do you think?
